#Text=The Boston Celtics ( 39 - 42 ) defeated the Toronto Raptors ( 48 - 33 ) 95 - 93 on Tuesday at the TD Garden in Boston .
#Text=Down two points with just over 10 seconds left in the game , Kyle Lowry brought the Raptors back to tie the Celtics after a driving layup .
#Text=It was the Celtics who came out with the last laugh though , as Jae Crowder hit a clutch jump shot with just under a second left in regulation to pull out the victory .

#Text=It was a solid victory for the Celtics , as they 're now going to go into the playoffs as the seventh seed in the Eastern Conference standings , meaning they 'll take on the Cleveland Cavaliers during the first round .

#Text=The Raptors , on the other hand , moved down into the fourth seed in the East , a game behind the Chicago Bulls , which would mean they could end up playing the fiffth - seeded Washington Wizards in their first playoff matchup .
#Text=It was the duo of Avery Bradley and Evan Turner that had the biggest impact in securing the win Tuesday .
#Text=Turner nearly came out with a triple - double , finishing with 14 points ( 7 - 14 FG ) , seven rebounds and nine assists .
#Text=It was n't all good for the forward though , as he did record seven turnovers as well .
#Text=He 's combined for 29 points and 14 assists over his last two games , and he 'll need to continue to play well if the Celtics want any chance at pulling off an upset during the playoffs .

#Text=Bradley recorded 14 points ( 5 - 11 FG , 1 - 5 3Pt , 3 - 3 FT ) of his own , to go along with three rebounds and two assists , but he ended up suffering a left quad contusion and was forced to leave the game .
#Text=He 'll likely sit Wednesday 's finale out in order to get healthy for their first playoff matchup .
#Text=Brandon Bass and Tyler Zeller were the other two starters in double figures .
#Text=Bass finished with 13 points ( 4 - 11 FG , 0 - 1 3Pt , 5 - 5 FT ) and nine rebounds , while Zeller added 12 points ( 5 - 11 FG , 2 - 2 FT ) and eight rebounds .

#Text=For the Raptors , Kyle Lowry went 6 - for - 20 from the field and 2 - for - 4 from the three - point line to match a team - high of 16 points , while also recording six rebounds and four assists .

#Text=Lowry has really struggled with his shot lately , combining to go just 9 - for - 34 from the field over his last two games , so he really needs to get things turned around if the Raptors want to have some success in the playoffs .

#Text=Despite struggling with his shot similar to Lowry , Louis Williams still posted 16 points ( 3 - 13 FG , 0 - 4 3Pt ) , as he was able to get to the free throw line 11 times , while converting on 10 - of - 11 .
#Text=Williams continues to be a great offensive option off the Raptors ' bench , averaging 21 points over his last six games .

#Text=Jonas Valanciunas nearly came up with a double - double , posting 10 points ( 4 - 8 FG , 2 - 4 FT ) , eight rebounds and two blocked shots , while Greivis Vasquez chipped in with 11 points ( 4 - 7 FG , 3 - 6 3Pt ) , five rebounds and seven assists .
#Text=The Celtics will close out the regular season on the road against the Milwaukee Bucks on Wednesday , while the Raptors will be at home against the Charlotte Hornets on Wednesday .
